{
  "texts": [
    "Evaluation of Pd-MpcWe evaluated Pd-Mpc by studying how it performs under a simulated city-scale drone deployment.",
    "To model the regulatory authority server, we used a Intel Core i7-7700 (3.60GHz) CPU with 16GB RAM, running Linux 5.11.0-37 (Ubuntu 20.04).",
    "To model the citizen's mobile device, we used a NVidia Xavier NX board with (ARMv8.2 64-bit 6-core CPU, with 8GB RAM), running Linux for Tegra [58].",
    "We chose this platform because there are no publicly-available MPC frameworks for Android devices in the public domain.",
    "To our knowledge PAL [65] is the only MPC framework for Android, but is not publicly available and supports an older version of Android."
  ]
}